PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4126
1 Delete lines 14 and 15 of the printed bill and insert:
2 “(b) An estimate of the total vehicle miles driven on the public highways
3 of this state based on the most recently available data on vehicle miles
4 traveled, set forth separately according to the following weight table:
5 “(A) Vehicles weighing 10,000 pounds or less.
6 “(B) Vehicles weighing more than 10,000 pounds and not more than 12,000
7 pounds.
8 “(C) Vehicles weighing more than 12,000 pounds and not more than 14,000
9 pounds.
10 “(D) Vehicles weighing more than 14,000 pounds and not more than 16,000
11 pounds.
12 “(E) Vehicles weighing more than 16,000 pounds and not more than 18,000
13 pounds.
14 “(F) Vehicles weighing more than 18,000 pounds and not more than 20,000
15 pounds.
16 “(G) Vehicles weighing more than 20,000 pounds and not more than 22,000
17 pounds.
18 “(H) Vehicles weighing more than 22,000 pounds and not more than 24,000
19 pounds.
20 “(I) Vehicles weighing more than 24,000 pounds and not more than 26,000
21 pounds.

1 “(J) Vehicles weighing more than 26,000 pounds.”.
2 Delete lines 24 through 26 and insert:
3 “SECTION 3. Notwithstanding the due date for submission of re-
4 ports under section 2 (1) of this 2026 Act, the Department of Trans-
5 portation shall submit the first report that is due after the effective
6 date of this 2026 Act not later than January 31, 2027.
7 “SECTION 4. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate
8 preservation of the public peace, health and not more than safety, an
9 emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect on its
10 passage.”.
